1
00:00:05,831 --> 00:00:08,095
[♪♪]

2
00:01:07,241 --> 00:01:09,634
<i>I LOVED HALLOWEEN.</i>

3
00:01:09,678 --> 00:01:11,375
<i>OKAY, NOT A HUGE
SURPRISE THERE.</i>

4
00:01:11,419 --> 00:01:14,770
<i>I MEAN, WHAT KID
DOESN'T LOVE HALLOWEEN?</i>

5
00:01:14,813 --> 00:01:19,296
<i>BUT MY DEVOTION TO THE DAY
WAS NOT
FOR THE OBVIOUS REASONS.</i>

6
00:01:19,340 --> 00:01:21,690
<i>I COULDN'T CARE LESS
ABOUT THE CANDY.</i>

7
00:01:21,733 --> 00:01:24,780
<i>AND I DIDN'T GIVE A SHIT
ABOUT THE COSTUMES.</i>

8
00:01:24,823 --> 00:01:29,045
<i>I LOVED HALLOWEEN
BECAUSE I LOVED LOOKING
INTO OTHER PEOPLE'S HOUSES.</i>

9
00:01:37,793 --> 00:01:39,751
WHY'S THE CANDY OUTSIDE?

10
00:01:39,795 --> 00:01:41,710
THEY PROBABLY DON'T WANT
TO BE DISTURBED, SWEETIE.

11
00:01:41,753 --> 00:01:43,755
BUT IT'S HALLOWEEN,
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
DISTURBING.

12
00:01:43,799 --> 00:01:45,061
MAYBE THEY'RE JUST NOT HOME.

13
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:46,802
THAT'S A BUNCH OF BULL--
THEY'RE HOME!

14
00:01:47,890 --> 00:01:48,978
[SIGHING][RINGING]

15
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:51,502
TRICK OR TREAT,
DAMNIT!

16
00:01:53,983 --> 00:01:55,941
[RINGING]

17
00:01:55,985 --> 00:01:59,206
JUST TAKE A PIECE OF CANDY
AND LET'S GO
TO THE NEXT HOUSE.

18
00:01:59,249 --> 00:02:01,773
HELLO!
I KNOW YOU'RE IN THERE!

19
00:02:01,817 --> 00:02:03,340
GEORGE, LISTEN
TO YOUR MOTHER.

20
00:02:05,864 --> 00:02:08,606
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.
EVERY OTHER KID
IS IN IT FOR THE CANDY.

21
00:02:08,650 --> 00:02:11,174
SO? SHE'S CURIOUS.
CURIOUS IS GOOD.

22
00:02:11,218 --> 00:02:13,655
HEY, GEORGIA,
I HAVE A FEELING
THE NEXT HOUSE

23
00:02:13,698 --> 00:02:16,092
IS GOING TO BE
GIVING OUT GUMMY WORMS.

24
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,486
MM-HMM. AND I THINK
THEY'RE GOING TO LET YOU
SEE INSIDE.

25
00:02:19,487 --> 00:02:21,010
THERE'S BARELY ANY FURNITURE.

26
00:02:21,967 --> 00:02:23,752
MAYBE SOME WEIRDO LIVES HERE.

27
00:02:23,795 --> 00:02:25,406
HONEY, YOU'RE BEING
THE WEIRDO.

28
00:02:25,449 --> 00:02:26,972
WE'RE LEAVING.
COME IF YOU WANT.

29
00:02:28,757 --> 00:02:29,714
FINE!

30
00:02:41,073 --> 00:02:42,162
BOO!

31
00:02:43,946 --> 00:02:46,601
<i>HALLOWEEN IS WHEN THE FREAKS
CAME OUT OF THE SHADOWS.</i>

32
00:02:47,993 --> 00:02:49,125
<i>NOW THAT I'M OLDER...</i>

33
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:50,866
<i>AND DEADER,</i>

34
00:02:50,909 --> 00:02:53,695
<i>I SEE THAT HALLOWEEN
IS AMATEUR NIGHT FOR DEATH.</i>

35
00:02:53,738 --> 00:02:56,088
<i>"OOH, LOOK AT ME,
I'M BLEEDING."</i>

36
00:02:56,132 --> 00:02:58,961
<i>"OOH, LOOK AT ME,
SOMEONE HIT ME WITH AN AX."</i>

37
00:02:59,004 --> 00:03:01,268
TRICK OR TREAT.TRICK OR TREAT.

38
00:03:01,311 --> 00:03:03,052
YOU KNOW,
I'VE SEEN ONE OF THOSE
IN REAL LIFE,

39
00:03:03,095 --> 00:03:04,096
AND LET ME
TELL YOU SOMETHING--

40
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:06,795
NOT SO FUNNY.

41
00:03:06,838 --> 00:03:09,406
I'M NOT A PRUDE.
IT'S JUST UNSEEMLY.

42
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:12,104
A MAN'S HOME IS
A MAN'S CASTLE.

43
00:03:12,148 --> 00:03:15,586
IN HIS CASTLE,
HE SHOULD BE ALLOWED
TO SWING FREE.

44
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:17,240
THERE ARE BOUNDARIES.

45
00:03:17,284 --> 00:03:19,677
MASON, OTHER PEOPLE
CAN SEE THEM.
WHY CAN'T YOU?

46
00:03:19,721 --> 00:03:21,113
NUDE IS NATURAL.

47
00:03:21,157 --> 00:03:22,811
NUDE IS NOW.

48
00:03:22,854 --> 00:03:26,075
I'M ABOUT TO EAT BREAKFAST,
SO CAN WE EASE UP
ON THE NAKED TALK?

49
00:03:26,118 --> 00:03:27,250
PLEASE?
THANK YOU.

50
00:03:27,294 --> 00:03:29,209
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO
SEE IT, GEORGIA.

51
00:03:29,252 --> 00:03:30,732
IT'S NOT HOW I WANTED
TO START MY DAY.

52
00:03:30,775 --> 00:03:33,213
WELL, YOU SCREAMING
AT 6:53 IN THE MORNING

53
00:03:33,256 --> 00:03:35,084
WAS NOT HOW I WANTED
TO START MINE.

54
00:03:35,127 --> 00:03:37,173
BY THE WAY,
YOU'RE NOT THE FIRST WOMAN

55
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:41,264
WHO HAS SHRIEKED AT THE SIGHT
OF THE LOCH NESS MONSTER
RISING TO THE SURFACE.

56
00:03:41,308 --> 00:03:42,744
DON'T FLATTER YOURSELF.

57
00:03:42,787 --> 00:03:45,312
OKAY, FOLKS,
TWO RULES STARTING
AS OF RIGHT NOW.

58
00:03:46,095 --> 00:03:47,618
ONE--

59
00:03:47,662 --> 00:03:50,447
BREAKFAST AT OUR HOUSE
IS NO LONGER
CLOTHING OPTIONAL.

60
00:03:50,491 --> 00:03:52,449
ALL MEALS.ALL MEALS.

61
00:03:52,493 --> 00:03:53,624
FINE.

62
00:03:53,668 --> 00:03:55,670
TWO, AND MOST IMPORTANT--

63
00:03:55,713 --> 00:03:57,280
YOU TOUCH
MY FUCKING POP TARTS AGAIN

64
00:03:57,324 --> 00:03:59,674
AND YOUR "MONSTER"
IS GOING TO GET IT
IN HIS SLEEP.

65
00:03:59,717 --> 00:04:02,677
FINE, AND F.Y.I., I LIKE
STRAWBERRY FROSTED THE BEST.

66
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,200
IN ADDITION
TO EATING MY GROCERIES,

67
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:05,984
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO START PROVIDING THEM.

68
00:04:06,028 --> 00:04:06,942
YOU NEED TO EARN YOUR KEEP.

69
00:04:06,985 --> 00:04:08,073
I--

70
00:04:08,117 --> 00:04:09,814
ALL RIGHT!

71
00:04:09,858 --> 00:04:11,729
ALL RIGHT...
I--I'LL DO SOME CHORES.

72
00:04:11,773 --> 00:04:13,644
OKAY, FINE, DO SOME CHORES.

73
00:04:14,689 --> 00:04:16,386
DO MY FUCKING LAUNDRY.

74
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:18,475
I DON'T THINK SO.
DO YOU LIKE CANDY?

75
00:04:18,519 --> 00:04:19,868
EVERYONE LIKES CANDY.

76
00:04:19,911 --> 00:04:20,999
EXCELLENT. WELL,
THIS IS WHAT I'M
GOING TO DO.

77
00:04:21,043 --> 00:04:22,958
I'M GOING TO GET
SO MUCH CANDY TONIGHT,

78
00:04:23,001 --> 00:04:25,743
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
A WHOLE YEAR'S SUPPLY
IN OUR HOUSE.

79
00:04:25,787 --> 00:04:27,049
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
SO MUCH CANDY,

80
00:04:27,092 --> 00:04:29,312
YOU'RE GOING TO BE BEGGING
FOR CANDY MERCY.

81
00:04:29,356 --> 00:04:30,835
OH, I'M GOING TO START NOW.
KIDS, OVER HERE.
KIDDIES, HERE.

82
00:04:30,879 --> 00:04:32,228
NO, MASON,
DON'T BRING CHILDREN
NEAR US.

83
00:04:32,272 --> 00:04:33,316
HI.

84
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:35,013
OKAY, LISTEN.

85
00:04:35,057 --> 00:04:37,668
WE'RE GOING TO PLAY
A LITTLE HALLOWEEN GAME.

86
00:04:37,712 --> 00:04:40,105
NOW, I'M GOING TO ASK YOU
A QUESTION,

87
00:04:40,149 --> 00:04:41,890
AND YOU ARE GOING TO
ANSWER ME.

88
00:04:41,933 --> 00:04:43,674
IF YOU GET IT RIGHT,
YOU GET A DOLLAR.

89
00:04:43,718 --> 00:04:45,502
IF YOU GET IT WRONG,
I GET YOUR CANDY. ALL RIGHT?

90
00:04:45,546 --> 00:04:46,938
RIGHT. QUESTION--

91
00:04:48,462 --> 00:04:50,812
WHAT ORIGINAL MEMBER
OF THE ROLLING STONES

92
00:04:50,855 --> 00:04:53,118
CROAKED WHILST HAVING
A DROWNING ACCIDENT?

93
00:04:53,597 --> 00:04:54,859
MICK JAGGER.

94
00:04:54,903 --> 00:04:56,818
NO, HE'S KIND OF ALIVE
AND STILL TOURING.

95
00:04:57,862 --> 00:05:00,343
KEITH MOON?NO! THAT'S THE FUCKING WHO.

96
00:05:01,170 --> 00:05:02,867
WHO?THE WHO.

97
00:05:02,911 --> 00:05:04,695
IT'S BRIAN JONES,
NOW HAND OVER THE CANDY.

98
00:05:07,481 --> 00:05:09,744
NOW PISS OFF.

99
00:05:09,787 --> 00:05:11,441
I PARTIED WITH HIM,
AND I REAPED HIM.

100
00:05:12,137 --> 00:05:13,661
YES!

101
00:05:13,704 --> 00:05:15,315
STEALING CANDY
FROM CHILDREN?

102
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:19,536
MM. CHALLENGING.

103
00:05:19,580 --> 00:05:20,929
YOU'VE COME
A LONG WAY, MASON.

104
00:05:20,972 --> 00:05:22,583
IT'S HALLOWEEN,
RUBY.

105
00:05:22,626 --> 00:05:24,628
WORSE THINGS
WILL HAPPEN TODAY.

106
00:05:24,672 --> 00:05:25,760
IN FACT, THEY WILL.

107
00:05:27,414 --> 00:05:29,154
YOU. YOU.

108
00:05:30,939 --> 00:05:32,680
AND YOU.

109
00:05:32,723 --> 00:05:33,855
GIVE ME
A LITTLE ROOM, HUH?

110
00:05:43,212 --> 00:05:44,344
AND YOU...

111
00:05:45,388 --> 00:05:47,259
MIGHT WANT
TO WEAR THIS.UM...

112
00:05:47,303 --> 00:05:49,871
I KNOW I'M THE YOUNGEST
ONE HERE,

113
00:05:49,914 --> 00:05:51,612
BUT I DON'T
TRICK-OR-TREAT.

114
00:05:51,655 --> 00:05:53,440
NO, NO.
REAPER LEGEND--

115
00:05:53,483 --> 00:05:56,617
THE DEAD WILL APPEAR
AS THEMSELVES
ON HALLOWEEN.

116
00:05:56,660 --> 00:05:58,793
SO, IN THEORY, I CAN BE...

117
00:05:58,836 --> 00:06:01,535
RECOGNIZED.I'VE NEVER BOUGHT THAT.

118
00:06:01,578 --> 00:06:04,451
I DON'T CARE
WHETHER YOU BUY IT OR NOT.

119
00:06:04,494 --> 00:06:06,844
OPEN YOURSELF TO THE
POSSIBILITY THAT THERE ARE
PEOPLE OUT THERE

120
00:06:06,888 --> 00:06:08,629
WHO KNEW YOU
WHEN YOU WERE ALIVE

121
00:06:08,672 --> 00:06:10,413
AND WHO CAN SEE YOU TODAY
AS YOU WERE.

122
00:06:10,457 --> 00:06:12,502
I'VE BEEN DEAD
FOR OVER 60 YEARS.

123
00:06:12,546 --> 00:06:13,764
I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU.

124
00:06:14,809 --> 00:06:16,376
SHE'S DEAD A YEAR,
IN HER HOMETOWN.

125
00:06:16,419 --> 00:06:18,160
YEAH, IT'S NONSENSE, OKAY?

126
00:06:18,203 --> 00:06:20,989
AND WHY WOULD YOU WANT TO
PUT THIS EXQUISITE FACE
BEHIND A MASK?

127
00:06:21,424 --> 00:06:22,817
YEAH.

128
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:25,950
AND THESE STRAPPY THINGS
GET CAUGHT IN MY HAIR.

129
00:06:25,994 --> 00:06:27,038
IT'S VERY PAINFUL.

130
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,432
[WHISTLES]

131
00:06:29,954 --> 00:06:31,347
WOW.WOW.

132
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,436
NICE...

133
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:36,091
I'M UNDERCOVER TODAY,
AND I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT.

134
00:06:36,134 --> 00:06:39,050
ROXY, YOUR DRESS
MAKES ME FEEL FUNNY
IN MY PANTS.

135
00:06:41,139 --> 00:06:43,446
I'M ARMED,
AND YOU'RE NOT.

136
00:06:43,490 --> 00:06:45,143
DO WE HAVE TO GO DOWN
THIS ROAD AGAIN?

137
00:06:45,187 --> 00:06:46,580
NO.JUST CURIOUS--

138
00:06:46,623 --> 00:06:47,972
WHERE IS YOUR FIREARM?

139
00:06:52,499 --> 00:06:53,500
OH.

140
00:06:54,979 --> 00:06:57,286
WHAT EXACTLY ARE YOU
SUPPOSED TO BE?

141
00:06:57,329 --> 00:07:00,811
I'M ROXY,
THE BAD-ASS WITCH
OF THE NORTHWEST.

142
00:07:06,251 --> 00:07:07,601
HEY...

143
00:07:07,644 --> 00:07:10,821
BOTH OF OUR POST-ITS
ARE AT 59 PAST THE HOUR.

144
00:07:10,865 --> 00:07:12,040
MINE, TOO.

145
00:07:12,083 --> 00:07:13,607
WHY ISN'T SHE
WEARING A MASK?

146
00:07:13,650 --> 00:07:14,869
FUCKS WITH HER HAIR.

147
00:07:15,913 --> 00:07:17,437
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.

148
00:07:20,265 --> 00:07:21,745
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.BYE.

149
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:24,748
HOW MUCH?

150
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,055
OKAY.BOO!

151
00:07:30,928 --> 00:07:32,234
KEEP THE CHANGE,
KIFFANY.

152
00:07:32,277 --> 00:07:34,584
IS THAT REAPER LEGEND
REALLY TRUE?

153
00:07:34,628 --> 00:07:38,022
WELL, IT'S AS TRUE
AS YOU WANT IT TO BE.

154
00:07:38,066 --> 00:07:40,024
WHAT, THAT'S IT?
THAT'S ALL YOU GOT?

155
00:07:40,068 --> 00:07:41,809
I COULD MARCH RIGHT UP
TO MY OLD HOUSE

156
00:07:41,852 --> 00:07:44,028
AND ASK MY SISTER
FOR A KIT KAT.

157
00:07:44,072 --> 00:07:45,290
YOU COULD.

158
00:07:45,334 --> 00:07:46,857
WHAT'S STOPPING ME?

159
00:07:46,901 --> 00:07:48,511
I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT IS STOPPING YOU?

160
00:07:54,735 --> 00:07:56,214
SOMETHING HAPPENED TO YOU.

161
00:07:57,302 --> 00:07:59,043
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

162
00:07:59,087 --> 00:08:01,045
YOU'RE THE PATERNAL ONE.

163
00:08:01,568 --> 00:08:03,178
IS THAT WHAT I AM?

164
00:08:03,221 --> 00:08:05,441
YES.
DAISY'S THE STARLET,

165
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:07,225
MASON'S THE SCREW-UP,
ROXY'S...

166
00:08:08,444 --> 00:08:09,924
ROXY, AND YOU'RE...

167
00:08:11,142 --> 00:08:12,274
YOU'RE THE DAD.

168
00:08:14,711 --> 00:08:16,757
WELL, PATERNAL DIDN'T TURN OUT
TO BE SUCH A GOOD GIG.

169
00:08:19,455 --> 00:08:21,675
YOU WANT ADVICE FROM ME,
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

170
00:08:25,679 --> 00:08:28,159
HEY, WEAR RUNNING SHOES TODAY.
TRICK-OR-TREATING'S
A REAL GRIND.

171
00:08:33,425 --> 00:08:34,252
BOO!

172
00:08:35,558 --> 00:08:36,777
I HAVE TO GO
TO HAPPY TIME.

173
00:08:37,778 --> 00:08:39,083
IT'S SUNDAY.

174
00:08:39,127 --> 00:08:41,085
I LEFT MY
RUNNING SHOES THERE.

175
00:08:41,129 --> 00:08:41,999
I'LL COME WITH YOU.

176
00:08:43,174 --> 00:08:44,393
ROXY'S THE MOTHER.

177
00:08:44,436 --> 00:08:45,829
EXCUSE ME?

178
00:08:45,873 --> 00:08:47,483
SHE REMINDS ME OF MY MOTHER.

179
00:08:49,964 --> 00:08:52,444
SHE REMINDS ME
OF MY MOTHER.

180
00:08:52,488 --> 00:08:54,359
WAS SHE A COP?

181
00:08:54,403 --> 00:08:55,360
SHE COULD HAVE BEEN.

182
00:09:00,365 --> 00:09:01,932
OH, THESE SEEDS
ARE GROSS.

183
00:09:02,672 --> 00:09:04,369
SLIMY.

184
00:09:04,413 --> 00:09:06,328
WAIT TILL
THEY'RE TOASTED.
YOU'LL LOVE THEM.

185
00:09:06,371 --> 00:09:07,547
WHY CAN'T I
CARVE THE PUMPKIN?

186
00:09:09,461 --> 00:09:10,941
MAYBE NEXT YEAR.

187
00:09:10,985 --> 00:09:13,117
THAT'S WHAT YOU SAID
LAST YEAR.

188
00:09:13,161 --> 00:09:14,945
WHY DON'T YOU GO GET
YOUR COSTUME READY
FOR TONIGHT?

189
00:09:14,989 --> 00:09:16,338
I'M NOT GOING
TRICK-OR-TREATING.

190
00:09:18,514 --> 00:09:20,168
BUT YOU LOVE CANDY.

191
00:09:20,908 --> 00:09:22,170
I'M OVER IT.

192
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:27,044
YOUR SISTER
WENT TRICK-OR-TREATING
EVERY YEAR,

193
00:09:27,654 --> 00:09:29,177
AND SHE TOOK YOU.

194
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,310
I'LL BET SHE'LL BE
OUT THERE TONIGHT.

195
00:09:32,354 --> 00:09:33,660
REGGIE.

196
00:09:33,703 --> 00:09:35,444
IT'S HALLOWEEN--

197
00:09:35,487 --> 00:09:37,489
THE NIGHT WHEN GHOSTS
WALK THE EARTH.

198
00:09:40,884 --> 00:09:43,147
OKAY, I'M BRINGING THIS UP
IN THERAPY TODAY.

199
00:09:43,191 --> 00:09:44,671
DANA'S COMING IN
AS A FAVOR.

200
00:09:46,063 --> 00:09:47,325
I WAS JUST KIDDING.

201
00:09:48,631 --> 00:09:49,937
OH. OKAY.

202
00:09:51,634 --> 00:09:52,679
WERE YOU?

203
00:09:55,986 --> 00:09:58,467
WE CAN GO
TRICK-OR-TREATING
TONIGHT IF YOU WANT.

204
00:09:58,510 --> 00:10:01,296
FINE. ARE YOU GOING TO WEAR
YOUR POCHAHONTAS OUTFIT?

205
00:10:01,339 --> 00:10:03,254
I THINK I'M GOING TO GO
AS A GHOST.

206
00:10:03,298 --> 00:10:04,386
WE DON'T HAVE
A GHOST COSTUME.

207
00:10:05,430 --> 00:10:07,955
GHOSTS DON'T WEAR COSTUMES.

208
00:10:07,998 --> 00:10:10,131
THEY LOOK JUST LIKE
YOU AND ME.

209
00:10:16,006 --> 00:10:18,356
<i>ONE HALLOWEEN,
WHEN I WAS A LITTLE KID,</i>

210
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,794
<i>MY DAD PULLED OUT A KNIFE
TO CARVE OUR PUMPKIN...</i>

211
00:10:22,186 --> 00:10:24,319
<i>I TOTALLY LOST IT,
I STARTED TO CRY,</i>

212
00:10:24,362 --> 00:10:26,408
<i>BEGGED HIM
NOT TO HURT THE PUMPKIN.</i>

213
00:10:26,451 --> 00:10:27,801
[MAN WHISTLING]

214
00:10:27,844 --> 00:10:30,978
<i>MY MOM AND DAD TOLD ME
TO CALM DOWN.</i>

215
00:10:31,021 --> 00:10:34,808
<i>THEY TOLD ME
THE SCARY STUFF ON HALLOWEEN
WAS ALL MAKE-BELIEVE,</i>

216
00:10:34,851 --> 00:10:37,201
<i>THAT NO ONE WOULD GET HURT,
LEAST OF ALL THE PUMPKIN.</i>

217
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:41,379
<i>I MEAN, THEY'RE YOUR PARENTS.</i>

218
00:10:41,423 --> 00:10:43,207
<i>YOU HAVE TO TRUST
YOUR PARENTS.</i>

219
00:10:45,253 --> 00:10:46,863
<i>AND THEN I LET THEM
KILL THE PUMPKIN.</i>

220
00:10:51,999 --> 00:10:53,609
WHAT THE FUCK?

221
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:55,263
EVERY YEAR. EVERY YEAR.

222
00:10:56,177 --> 00:10:58,353
I HATE HALLOWEEN.

223
00:10:58,396 --> 00:11:00,181
EVERY JACKASS
WITH A 50-CENT MASK

224
00:11:00,224 --> 00:11:02,574
THINKS HE HAS A LICENSE
FOR MAYHEM AND TOMFOOLERY.

225
00:11:02,618 --> 00:11:05,665
ALREADY TODAY,
I HAD A DEAD CAT

226
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:07,405
AND A BAG
OF FLAMING SHIT

227
00:11:07,449 --> 00:11:09,364
ON SOME OLD LADY'S
DOORSTEP.

228
00:11:09,407 --> 00:11:11,105
FLAMING SHIT.

229
00:11:11,148 --> 00:11:13,237
THAT'S A CLASSIC.

230
00:11:13,281 --> 00:11:15,457
THIS PRINCESS GARB
IS SO UNCOMFORTABLE.

231
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,937
I'M TAKING THIS OFF.

232
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:19,591
NO, NO, NO, ROXY,
THAT MAKES THE
WHOLE ENSEMBLE.

233
00:11:19,635 --> 00:11:21,593
GOD, YOU LOOK GREAT.

234
00:11:21,637 --> 00:11:23,683
MAYBE I WILL PUT
A COSTUME TOGETHER.

235
00:11:23,726 --> 00:11:25,162
BE RIGHT BACK.

236
00:11:25,206 --> 00:11:26,468
IF YOU KEEP EATING
ALL THE CANDY,

237
00:11:26,511 --> 00:11:28,035
HOW ARE WE GOING TO HAVE
A YEAR'S SUPPLY LEFT

238
00:11:28,078 --> 00:11:30,080
BY THE END
OF THE EVENING?

239
00:11:30,124 --> 00:11:32,692
WELL, IF YOU'LL COME WITH ME
ON MY LITTLE TRIP
OF CONTROLLED CHAOS,

240
00:11:32,735 --> 00:11:33,910
THEN YOU'LL SEE.

241
00:11:35,999 --> 00:11:37,305
I'M IN.

242
00:11:37,348 --> 00:11:39,176
JUST OUT OF RESPECT
FOR THE EVENING.

243
00:11:39,220 --> 00:11:40,090
YEAH?

244
00:11:42,136 --> 00:11:44,442
IT'S HOODLUMS LIKE YOU
THAT MAKE MY JOB
SO DIFFICULT.

245
00:11:44,921 --> 00:11:47,141
OH, ROXY.

246
00:11:47,184 --> 00:11:48,751
LET ME EXPLAIN
SOMETHING TO YOU.

247
00:11:48,795 --> 00:11:52,102
THE UNIVERSE,
IN ALL OF ITS
INFINITE WISDOM,

248
00:11:52,146 --> 00:11:53,669
ALLOWS THE FORCES
OF DESTRUCTION

249
00:11:53,713 --> 00:11:55,584
ONE EVENING A YEAR

250
00:11:55,627 --> 00:11:57,499
TO HAVE FULL REIGN.

251
00:11:57,542 --> 00:12:00,632
ON ALL HALLOWS' EVE,
YOU CAN GET AWAY
WITH ANYTHING.

252
00:12:00,676 --> 00:12:01,938
CAN WE LOOK IN
PEOPLE'S HOUSES?

253
00:12:01,982 --> 00:12:03,679
YES.[BOTH SNICKERING]

254
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:05,159
CAN'T BLOODY WAIT!

255
00:12:05,463 --> 00:12:06,595
OOH.

256
00:12:07,901 --> 00:12:09,293
OH. ONE CAN GET AWAY
WITH MURDER.

257
00:12:12,340 --> 00:12:13,733
[MAN WHISTLING]

258
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:48,332
<i>I NEVER BELIEVED
IN FAIRIES.</i>

259
00:12:48,376 --> 00:12:50,552
<i>I NEVER CLAPPED
FOR TINKERBELL,</i>

260
00:12:50,595 --> 00:12:53,511
<i>AND I WAS NEVER SCARED
OF GHOSTS.</i>

261
00:12:53,555 --> 00:12:56,601
<i>BUT MAYBE THERE WAS MORE
TO HALLOWEEN THAN
MILK DUDS AND VANDALISM.</i>

262
00:12:58,429 --> 00:13:00,736
<i>MAYBE THERE WAS A REASON
FOR ME TO STAY IN THE SHADOWS.</i>

263
00:13:03,347 --> 00:13:05,523
<i>NOW, THAT'S ALMOST
DEFINITELY BULLSHIT.</i>

264
00:13:06,394 --> 00:13:07,830
HELLO, HAPPY TIME!

265
00:13:07,874 --> 00:13:08,918
SHH!

266
00:13:12,748 --> 00:13:14,968
IT'S SO STRANGE
THAT YOU WERE HERE, MILLIE.

267
00:13:15,011 --> 00:13:16,186
I AM HERE.

268
00:13:16,230 --> 00:13:18,667
NO, I MEAN BEFORE.

269
00:13:20,538 --> 00:13:22,279
NOW IT'S ALMOST LIKE
YOU'RE HAUNTING THE PLACE.

270
00:13:23,890 --> 00:13:25,935
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

271
00:13:25,979 --> 00:13:28,372
I AM STEALING THESE
FOR CANDY-GATHERING
PURPOSES.

272
00:13:31,723 --> 00:13:34,639
WELL, COULD YOU EASE UP
ON THE LARCENY?
I WORK HERE.

273
00:13:34,683 --> 00:13:37,773
I AM SIMPLY TESTING
FOR CANDY-GATHERING CAPACITY.

274
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:40,471
WE HAVE A WINNER.

275
00:13:41,385 --> 00:13:42,691
LOVELY.

276
00:13:42,734 --> 00:13:44,562
I WAS WATCHING T.V.
LAST NIGHT,

277
00:13:44,606 --> 00:13:48,740
SOME COPS AND ROBBERS
AND LAWYER BULLSHIT.

278
00:13:48,784 --> 00:13:51,134
YEAH, I KNOW, I HEARD YOU.
YOU WOKE ME UP.

279
00:13:51,178 --> 00:13:53,267
IT WAS SOME  <i>LAW AND ORDER
RERUN BULLSHIT,</i>

280
00:13:53,310 --> 00:13:55,443
AND, UH,
THERE WAS A DETECTIVE

281
00:13:55,486 --> 00:13:57,619
ASKING QUESTIONS
TO A PERP, RIGHT?

282
00:13:57,662 --> 00:14:00,013
AND IT ALWAYS
BLOODY ANNOYS ME
SO FUCKING MUCH,

283
00:14:00,056 --> 00:14:01,318
BECAUSE IT'S THE SAME
FUCKING QUESTION

284
00:14:01,362 --> 00:14:02,537
AGAIN AND AGAIN
AND AGAIN.

285
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:04,495
"DID YOU KNOW
THE DECEASED?"

286
00:14:04,539 --> 00:14:09,196
EXACTLY--
"DID YOU KNOW THE DECEASED?"

287
00:14:09,239 --> 00:14:13,722
COME ON. I MEAN, EVERYBODY
IN THE WHOLE FUCKING WORLD
KNOWS THE ANSWER IS "NO."

288
00:14:13,765 --> 00:14:15,028
THE ANSWER
IS ALWAYS "NO."

289
00:14:15,071 --> 00:14:17,508
ALWAYS "NO."
NO, NO, NO, NO.OKAY, I GOT IT.

290
00:14:17,552 --> 00:14:20,337
I THINK THEY SHOULD ASK US
THAT QUESTION.

291
00:14:20,381 --> 00:14:22,426
"DID YOU KNOW THE DECEASED?"
"NO, I DIDN'T KNOW
THE BLOODY DECEASED,

292
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:24,124
"BECAUSE
I'VE JUST MET HER

293
00:14:24,167 --> 00:14:26,387
"I'M ABOUT TO REAP HER,
AND SHE'S GOING TO DIE
IN THREE MINUTES."

294
00:14:28,998 --> 00:14:30,130
LIKE YOU DID, HERE.

295
00:14:30,173 --> 00:14:32,523
I WAS HERE A COUPLE OF HOURS.

296
00:14:33,829 --> 00:14:35,352
A MORNING, ACTUALLY,

297
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,920
AND NO ONE KNEW ME.

298
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:44,971
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW
THE DECEASED.
NEVER HAVE.

299
00:14:45,014 --> 00:14:47,321
YEAH, ME EITHER.

300
00:14:47,364 --> 00:14:50,063
I ONLY WANT TO KNOW
PEOPLE WHO'VE BEEN DEAD
A LONG TIME.

301
00:14:50,106 --> 00:14:52,500
ME, TOO.
EXCEPT FOR YOU.

302
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:58,027
[GASPS]

303
00:15:01,335 --> 00:15:03,554
NICE COSTUME, CRYSTAL.

304
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:06,035
SPOOKY.

305
00:15:06,079 --> 00:15:07,297
NICE MASK, MILLIE.

306
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:09,909
THANKS.

307
00:15:12,389 --> 00:15:14,174
WHAT'VE YOU
GOT THERE, CRYSTAL?

308
00:15:14,739 --> 00:15:15,784
NOTHING.

309
00:15:15,827 --> 00:15:18,134
IS IT A...
TRICK-OR-TREATING MAP?

310
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:24,314
HAVE YOU GOT
PRIME CANDY ZONES
HIGHLIGHTED?

311
00:15:26,882 --> 00:15:27,839
MASON,
LET'S GO NOW.

312
00:15:30,016 --> 00:15:32,061
HAPPY HALLOWEEN, CRYSTAL.

313
00:15:32,105 --> 00:15:33,541
LET'S GO, MASON.

314
00:15:33,584 --> 00:15:34,585
[♪♪]

315
00:15:48,121 --> 00:15:51,298
DEATH IS LIKE GOING TO
YOUR FIRST HAUNTED HOUSE
WHEN YOU WERE A KID...

316
00:15:52,125 --> 00:15:54,388
[WHISTLING]

317
00:15:54,431 --> 00:15:57,391
<i>YOU HAD TO WALK THROUGH IT
TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT STUFF WAS REALLY SCARY,</i>

318
00:15:58,435 --> 00:16:01,264
<i>AND WHAT STUFF
WAS JUST IN YOUR HEAD.</i>

319
00:16:01,308 --> 00:16:03,484
SO, HOW ARE WE
ON THIS HALLOWEEN SUNDAY?

320
00:16:09,142 --> 00:16:10,708
HOW ARE YOU FEELING
ABOUT THE DOG?

321
00:16:10,752 --> 00:16:12,406
THE DOG HAS A NAME.

322
00:16:13,581 --> 00:16:14,408
J.D.

323
00:16:15,887 --> 00:16:17,411
HOW ARE YOU FEELING
ABOUT J.D.?

324
00:16:19,891 --> 00:16:21,023
WHERE'S THE CANDY?

325
00:16:21,545 --> 00:16:22,938
REGGIE.

326
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:25,462
WHAT? CRAZY GIRLS DON'T NEED
A LITTLE CHOCOLATE?

327
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:31,468
YOU KNOW, REGGIE,
HOLIDAYS CAN BE
A LOT OF FUN,

328
00:16:31,512 --> 00:16:34,036
BUT THEY'RE ALSO
EMOTIONALLY DIFFICULT,

329
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:36,299
AND IT'S HARD NOT TO THINK
ABOUT YOUR FAMILY.

330
00:16:37,387 --> 00:16:38,736
ABOUT GEORGE.

331
00:16:41,870 --> 00:16:43,350
WELL, DID GEORGE
LIKE HALLOWEEN?

332
00:16:47,702 --> 00:16:49,008
GEORGE LOVED HALLOWEEN.

333
00:16:50,618 --> 00:16:52,533
SHE LIKED SPYING
ON OTHER PEOPLE.

334
00:16:55,362 --> 00:16:58,539
REGGIE THINKS THAT
GEORGE CONTINUES TO SPY
ON OTHER PEOPLE.

335
00:17:02,412 --> 00:17:03,631
SHE THINKS THAT
SHE'S A GHOST.

336
00:17:05,024 --> 00:17:06,547
IS THAT TRUE, REGGIE?

337
00:17:06,590 --> 00:17:08,027
DO YOU THINK
YOUR SISTER, GEORGE,
IS A GHOST?

338
00:17:08,940 --> 00:17:10,507
NO.

339
00:17:10,551 --> 00:17:12,205
YES, YOU DO THINK
SHE'S A GHOST.

340
00:17:12,248 --> 00:17:14,555
SHE THINKS
SHE'S A GHOST.

341
00:17:14,598 --> 00:17:16,557
NO, I DON'T.
I'M NOT CRAZY.

342
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:18,820
I BELIEVE IN GHOSTS.
DO YOU THINK
THAT MAKES ME CRAZY?

343
00:17:20,691 --> 00:17:22,519
I'D LIKE TO TALK
ABOUT MY PARENTS' DIVORCE

344
00:17:22,563 --> 00:17:24,739
AND HOW THAT'S DESTROYED
MY CHILDHOOD.

345
00:17:24,782 --> 00:17:27,350
I'M PAYING
$160 AN HOUR HERE, OKAY?

346
00:17:27,394 --> 00:17:28,830
AND I WOULD LIKE
TO DISCUSS THE FACT

347
00:17:28,873 --> 00:17:30,701
THAT REGGIE THINKS
HER SISTER IS
LIVING AMONG US.

348
00:17:30,745 --> 00:17:32,268
I DON'T THINK
GEORGE IS A GHOST.

349
00:17:32,312 --> 00:17:33,922
SHE'S LYING.NO, I'M NOT.

350
00:17:33,965 --> 00:17:35,358
UH--I DID.

351
00:17:36,794 --> 00:17:37,578
BUT I CHANGED MY MIND.

352
00:17:41,277 --> 00:17:44,106
OKAY.

353
00:17:44,150 --> 00:17:46,804
DO YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'VE GOT A SECRET STASH
OF LITTLE KIT KATS

354
00:17:46,848 --> 00:17:48,850
IN THE OTHER ROOM,
UNDER THE COFFEE TABLE.

355
00:17:48,893 --> 00:17:49,938
WANT TO GO GRAB A FEW?

356
00:17:50,547 --> 00:17:51,635
SURE.

357
00:17:59,948 --> 00:18:01,732
JOY...

358
00:18:01,776 --> 00:18:04,561
I UNDERSTAND
YOUR FRUSTRATION, I DO,

359
00:18:04,605 --> 00:18:06,215
BUT I REALLY WANT
TO ENCOURAGE YOU

360
00:18:06,259 --> 00:18:09,697
TO NOT TO PUT SO MUCH
PRESSURE ON YOURSELF
OR ON REGGIE.

361
00:18:09,740 --> 00:18:12,787
JUST TRY TO LET THE PROCESS
BE A LITTLE MORE ORGANIC.

362
00:18:14,528 --> 00:18:16,399
I CAN'T AFFORD ORGANIC.

363
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:19,968
DANA, YOU'RE
A VERY GOOD THERAPIST,

364
00:18:20,925 --> 00:18:23,145
YOU'RE A VERY SMART WOMAN,

365
00:18:23,189 --> 00:18:25,060
BUT I CAN'T AFFORD
TO COME HERE.

366
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:27,018
I CAN'T EVEN AFFORD
TO PARK HERE.

367
00:18:27,062 --> 00:18:29,804
OKAY, MAYBE WE CAN WORK OUT
SOME KIND OF A SLIDING SCALE.

368
00:18:34,025 --> 00:18:35,331
I DON'T REALLY THINK
THAT THERAPY

369
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:36,680
IS GOING TO BRING
MY DAUGHTER BACK.

370
00:18:40,031 --> 00:18:41,120
WHICH DAUGHTER
ARE YOU TRYING
TO BRING BACK?

371
00:19:00,008 --> 00:19:01,966
YOU'RE A LITTLE TALLER
THAN THE OTHER
TRICK-OR-TREATERS.

372
00:19:02,967 --> 00:19:05,231
CANDY BAR OR FRUIT ROLL-UP?

373
00:19:05,274 --> 00:19:06,362
HOW ABOUT
A MOMENT OF YOUR TIME?

374
00:19:14,022 --> 00:19:15,154
NO SALES!

375
00:19:15,197 --> 00:19:16,938
I'M NOT SELLING ANYTHING.

376
00:19:17,634 --> 00:19:18,679
GO AWAY.

377
00:19:21,290 --> 00:19:23,336
I'M WITH, UH,
CANDY BUSTERS, INC.

378
00:19:23,379 --> 00:19:26,600
I'M JUST TRYING
TO EDUCATE THE PUBLIC
ON THE PERILS OF SUGAR.

379
00:19:26,643 --> 00:19:28,428
YOU PICKED
THE WRONG NIGHT!

380
00:19:28,471 --> 00:19:30,343
WELL...

381
00:19:30,386 --> 00:19:33,128
IT'S ONE OF THE FEW NIGHTS
PEOPLE WILL OPEN THEIR DOOR
TO STRANGERS.

382
00:19:34,434 --> 00:19:35,870
QUESTION ONE...

383
00:19:37,001 --> 00:19:38,699
RATE THE APPLE
AS A HALLOWEEN TREAT--

384
00:19:38,742 --> 00:19:40,527
HEALTHY ALTERNATIVE
OR LIBERAL COP-OUT?

385
00:19:44,270 --> 00:19:45,619
COP-OUT.
NEXT QUESTION.

386
00:19:45,662 --> 00:19:47,403
LET ME GET YOUR NAME. UH...

387
00:19:49,013 --> 00:19:50,232
M. FELDMAN?

388
00:19:50,276 --> 00:19:51,625
JOSIE FELDMAN.

389
00:19:58,632 --> 00:19:59,633
LAST QUESTION...

390
00:20:01,461 --> 00:20:04,203
DID YOU KNOW CANDY
KILLS MORE PEOPLE
THAN CIGARETTES?

391
00:20:05,378 --> 00:20:06,640
I DON'T BELIEVE THAT.

392
00:20:09,991 --> 00:20:10,905
GOOD LUCK WITH YOUR SURVEY.

393
00:20:11,862 --> 00:20:13,386
WHERE'RE YOUR FOLKS?

394
00:20:13,429 --> 00:20:15,344
THEY'RE IN BARBADOS,
TRYING TO RECAPTURE
THEIR YOUTH.

395
00:20:16,258 --> 00:20:17,564
WELL...

396
00:20:17,607 --> 00:20:20,523
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
TAKE IN THESE NEWSPAPERS.

397
00:20:22,699 --> 00:20:25,789
CRIMINALS SEE THIS,
IT'S LIKE AN INVITATION.

398
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:27,182
COME ON.
THIS NEIGHBORHOOD?

399
00:20:32,187 --> 00:20:33,232
YOU HAVE A LAME JOB.

400
00:20:35,059 --> 00:20:36,365
I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR YOUR TIME.

401
00:20:36,409 --> 00:20:38,411
HEY, YOU WANT TO TAKE
SOME CANDY FOR YOUR KID?

402
00:20:38,454 --> 00:20:39,716
I DON'T HAVE A CHILD.COME ON.

403
00:20:40,717 --> 00:20:42,197
TAKE A SNICKERS
FOR THE ROAD.

404
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:43,111
SUGAR ROCKS.

405
00:20:45,331 --> 00:20:46,332
CAN I GIVE YOU
SOME ADVICE?

406
00:20:46,941 --> 00:20:48,029
SURE.

407
00:20:48,072 --> 00:20:49,248
ENJOY THAT CIGARETTE.

408
00:20:55,428 --> 00:20:59,301
<i>IN A WAY,
DEATH WAS KIND OF LIKE
A DOOR-TO-DOOR SALESMAN.</i>

409
00:20:59,345 --> 00:21:02,043
<i>MOST PEOPLE
WEREN'T TOO INTERESTED
IN WHAT WE WERE SELLING.</i>

410
00:21:02,086 --> 00:21:04,306
[WHISTLING]

411
00:21:04,350 --> 00:21:07,657
<i>OR THEY JUST DIDN'T
WANT TO MAKE THAT KIND
OF LONG-TERM COMMITMENT.</i>

412
00:21:08,354 --> 00:21:09,485
[KNOCKING]

413
00:21:15,578 --> 00:21:17,058
[THUD][SCREAMING]

414
00:21:17,101 --> 00:21:18,277
[RUSTLING]

415
00:21:22,237 --> 00:21:23,238
[DOOR CLOSES]

416
00:21:27,895 --> 00:21:29,288
[WHISTLING]

417
00:21:29,331 --> 00:21:30,898
<i>SO WE TRICK THEM.</i>

418
00:21:32,378 --> 00:21:33,727
[WHISTLING]

419
00:21:40,255 --> 00:21:41,561
YOU OKAY?

420
00:21:45,086 --> 00:21:46,174
COME ON.

421
00:21:48,132 --> 00:21:51,135
YOU THINK
YOU'RE TOUGH,
DON'T YOU?

422
00:21:51,179 --> 00:21:54,617
WHAT?YOU THINK YOU'RE A BAD ASS
IN YOUR LITTLE GET-UP.

423
00:21:54,661 --> 00:21:55,749
I COULD HAVE
PLAYED A COP, ROXY,

424
00:21:55,792 --> 00:21:57,446
A COP WITH
A HEART OF GOLD.

425
00:21:57,490 --> 00:21:59,622
IT'S NOT THE OUTFIT, DAISY.

426
00:21:59,666 --> 00:22:00,884
BEING TOUGH IS IN HERE.

427
00:22:00,928 --> 00:22:02,712
I'M TOUGH.OH, YEAH, REAL TOUGH.

428
00:22:03,452 --> 00:22:05,280
YOU'RE REAL IMPOSING.

429
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:07,369
IT'S VERY EASY
FOR YOU, ROXY.
YOU ARE ARMED.

430
00:22:08,457 --> 00:22:10,067
I NEED A GUN, TOO.

431
00:22:10,981 --> 00:22:12,418
A GIRL NEEDS ACCESSORIES.

432
00:22:12,461 --> 00:22:15,116
THE ONLY ACCESSORY I HAVE
IS MY ATTITUDE.

433
00:22:15,159 --> 00:22:16,335
OH, THEN, UH,
GIVE ME YOUR GUN.

434
00:22:16,378 --> 00:22:17,858
NO.PLEASE?

435
00:22:17,901 --> 00:22:19,686
NO.GIVE ME THE GUN.
GIVE ME THE GUN.

436
00:22:19,729 --> 00:22:20,817
GIVE ME THE GUN
GIVE ME THE GUN.

437
00:22:20,861 --> 00:22:22,732
JESUS CHRIST,
YOU'RE LIKE MASON.

438
00:22:22,776 --> 00:22:23,907
YOU ARE NOT A COP.

439
00:22:23,951 --> 00:22:26,083
AND YOU'RE NOT
A PRINCESS.

440
00:22:26,127 --> 00:22:27,433
AND DON'T YOU
FUCKING FORGET IT.

441
00:22:28,216 --> 00:22:29,957
THANK YOU.

442
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,525
OH, YOU FORGOT
TO CHARGE ME
FOR MY COFFEE.

443
00:22:32,568 --> 00:22:33,787
COFFEE'S FREE FOR COPS.

444
00:22:35,832 --> 00:22:37,747
SEE THE KIND
OF AN ACTRESS I AM?

445
00:22:37,791 --> 00:22:39,009
IT'S JUST EFFORTLESS.

446
00:22:40,184 --> 00:22:41,621
YEAH, IT WAS.

447
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:46,190
HEY, OLD MAN,

448
00:22:46,234 --> 00:22:47,801
TAKE A PICTURE,
IT LASTS LONGER.

449
00:22:52,022 --> 00:22:53,589
YOU SEE, ROXY?

450
00:22:53,633 --> 00:22:55,417
TAKE AWAY THE UNIFORM,
YOU'RE JUST ANOTHER
PRETTY FACE.

451
00:22:55,461 --> 00:22:57,027
YOU HAVE NO AUTHORITY.

452
00:22:58,159 --> 00:22:59,552
AHEM.

453
00:22:59,595 --> 00:23:02,293
HEY. YOU GONNA
STAND THERE GAWKING

454
00:23:02,337 --> 00:23:05,384
OR AM I GOING TO HAVE
TO DRAG YOUR ASS
TO THE STATION HOUSE?

455
00:23:05,427 --> 00:23:07,473
THIS IS FUN.

456
00:23:07,516 --> 00:23:10,258
PERHAPS YOU DIDN'T HEAR ME,
GRANDPA, I SAID--

457
00:23:10,301 --> 00:23:11,520
DAISY ADAIR.

458
00:23:15,437 --> 00:23:18,048
I'M SORRY,
I DON'T KNOW WHO THAT IS.

459
00:23:18,092 --> 00:23:20,486
<i>GONE WITH THE WIND.
SHE DIED DURING THE FILMING.</i>

460
00:23:21,530 --> 00:23:23,445
YOU'RE THE SPITTING IMAGE
OF HER.

461
00:23:23,489 --> 00:23:24,490
OH.

462
00:23:25,404 --> 00:23:27,536
WELL, GOOD FOR ME.

463
00:23:27,580 --> 00:23:31,105
I USED TO SEE MISS ADAIR
COME INTO THE STORK CLUB
EVERY NIGHT.

464
00:23:31,148 --> 00:23:33,281
USUALLY WITH
A DIFFERENT GENTLEMAN.

465
00:23:33,324 --> 00:23:35,196
ALL OF THEM,
OR MOST OF THEM, STARS.

466
00:23:35,849 --> 00:23:37,807
WELL, I'M NOT HER.

467
00:23:39,374 --> 00:23:40,767
OBVIOUSLY.

468
00:23:45,511 --> 00:23:47,600
HALLOWEEN
IS ONE FUCKED-UP DAY.

469
00:23:54,607 --> 00:23:55,825
GIVE ME THE GUN.

470
00:23:59,133 --> 00:24:01,396
THIS LOOKS LIKE
A CHOCOLATE HOUSE,
MAYBE EVEN CARAMEL.

471
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,919
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

472
00:24:02,963 --> 00:24:05,313
THE NICE DECORATIONS
AND CARAMEL-CHOCOLATE
WRAPPER.

473
00:24:05,356 --> 00:24:07,489
GET OUT
OF THE WAY! OI!
WAIT YOUR FUCKING TURN.

474
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:09,099
GET TO THE BACK!I'M NOT SCARED OF YOU.

475
00:24:10,231 --> 00:24:11,319
YOU EITHER.

476
00:24:11,362 --> 00:24:12,494
YOU'RE THREE-
AND-A-HALF-FEET TALL

477
00:24:12,538 --> 00:24:14,322
WITH AN EARRING
AND A SASH,
SO BACK OFF.

478
00:24:14,365 --> 00:24:15,366
YEAH.

479
00:24:22,243 --> 00:24:25,768
OOH. WHAT SCARY CREATURES
HAVE COME TO MY DOOR?

480
00:24:25,812 --> 00:24:27,074
THAT'S FOR US, THEN?
CHEERS.

481
00:24:27,117 --> 00:24:28,858
UH, MASON--
DRY... ICE.

482
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:35,996
[MASON GASPING]

483
00:24:43,699 --> 00:24:45,005
JESUS, THAT WAS COLD.

484
00:24:46,746 --> 00:24:48,225
AND WHAT ARE YOU?

485
00:24:48,269 --> 00:24:49,575
A GHOST.

486
00:24:49,618 --> 00:24:50,880
AH. AND YOU?

487
00:24:52,099 --> 00:24:53,143
GHOST.

488
00:24:53,187 --> 00:24:55,232
GOOD JOB, GUYS.
WAY TO GO ALL OUT.

489
00:24:55,276 --> 00:24:57,583
"A" FOR EFFORT.THANK YOU.

490
00:24:57,626 --> 00:24:59,193
CAN WE HAVE
SOME BLOODY CANDY NOW,
OR WHAT?

491
00:24:59,236 --> 00:25:00,020
MM.

492
00:25:02,239 --> 00:25:03,371
GO FOR IT.

493
00:25:03,414 --> 00:25:05,373
OI! GET OUT OF HERE.
COME ON, PISS OFF.

494
00:25:06,548 --> 00:25:08,028
OH... HI, FRANK.

495
00:25:09,682 --> 00:25:11,118
DEBRA'S IN THE ZEBRA ROOM.

496
00:25:25,741 --> 00:25:27,308
OH, THAT'S JUST NOT RIGHT.

497
00:25:36,317 --> 00:25:37,361
[DOORBELL RINGING]

498
00:25:39,233 --> 00:25:41,191
HAPPY HALLOWEEN!

499
00:25:41,235 --> 00:25:43,542
OBVIOUSLY, I'M A COUPLE
YEARS PAST
TRICK-OR-TREATING AGE,

500
00:25:43,585 --> 00:25:46,980
BUT I HAD TO
COMPLIMENT YOU ON THESE
GORGEOUS DECORATIONS.

501
00:25:47,023 --> 00:25:49,199
MAY I OFFER YOU
MY OREGANO-DUSTED
PUMPKIN SEEDS?

502
00:25:49,939 --> 00:25:50,984
AH!

503
00:25:53,421 --> 00:25:54,422
LOVELY.

504
00:25:55,815 --> 00:25:57,207
YOU MUST BE MRS. CLARK.

505
00:25:57,251 --> 00:25:58,731
YOU'RE A
NEIGHBORHOOD LEGEND.

506
00:25:58,774 --> 00:26:00,036
YOU CAN CALL ME KATIE.

507
00:26:01,168 --> 00:26:03,039
YOU DO BEAUTIFUL
WORK, KATIE.

508
00:26:06,173 --> 00:26:09,002
ARE THERE ANY PROBLEMS
IN THE AREA, OFFICER?

509
00:26:09,045 --> 00:26:10,264
TELL ME THOSE
AWFUL STUART BOYS

510
00:26:10,307 --> 00:26:12,222
DIDN'T DEFECATE
IN MY WISHING WELL AGAIN.

511
00:26:12,266 --> 00:26:14,877
NO, NO, JUST MAKING SURE
EVERYONE'S SAFE.

512
00:26:14,921 --> 00:26:16,531
KIDS TODAY ARE
SO ILL-MANNERED.

513
00:26:16,575 --> 00:26:17,619
HOOLIGANS.

514
00:26:17,663 --> 00:26:20,187
I ADORE HALLOWEEN.
[CHUCKLES]

515
00:26:20,230 --> 00:26:22,189
AND I WILL CONTINUE
TO CREATE

516
00:26:22,232 --> 00:26:25,235
ELEGANT DECORATIONS
AND HEALTHY SNACKS

517
00:26:25,279 --> 00:26:26,410
UNTIL THE DAY I DIE.

518
00:26:28,108 --> 00:26:29,152
GOOD LUCK WITH THAT.

519
00:26:31,024 --> 00:26:32,242
[WHISTLING]

520
00:26:36,464 --> 00:26:38,031
[DOORBELL RINGING]

521
00:26:53,133 --> 00:26:54,700
I JUST CLEANED
THOSE CUPBOARDS.

522
00:26:54,743 --> 00:26:56,005
PLEASE DON'T TOUCH THEM.

523
00:26:57,180 --> 00:27:00,401
STOP CLEANING.
I'M HUNGRY.

524
00:27:00,444 --> 00:27:03,012
HONEY, YOU KNOW
I'M GOING TO START
SHOWING THE HOUSE AGAIN.

525
00:27:05,101 --> 00:27:06,450
I KNOW YOU DON'T LIKE IT.

526
00:27:07,234 --> 00:27:08,627
THAT'S JUST HOW THINGS ARE.

527
00:27:10,063 --> 00:27:11,325
KNOCK KNOCK.

528
00:27:14,850 --> 00:27:16,069
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.

529
00:27:16,112 --> 00:27:17,461
HEY, SUZANNE.

530
00:27:20,464 --> 00:27:21,901
SUGAR SKULL?

531
00:27:21,944 --> 00:27:23,206
OH.HMM?

532
00:27:23,903 --> 00:27:25,165
I JUST HAD LUNCH.

533
00:27:27,341 --> 00:27:28,777
SO HOW'RE YOU
DOING, REGGIE?

534
00:27:30,126 --> 00:27:31,214
I'M FINE.

535
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,828
SO SORRY TO HEAR
ABOUT YOUR DOGGIE.

536
00:27:36,742 --> 00:27:38,004
THANKS.

537
00:27:39,658 --> 00:27:41,224
SO, THESE...

538
00:27:41,268 --> 00:27:42,443
ARE FOR <i>
DIA DE LOS MUERTOS--</i>

539
00:27:43,879 --> 00:27:45,751
DAY OF THE DEAD.

540
00:27:45,794 --> 00:27:48,405
IT'S SORT OF
THE MEXICAN VERSION
OF HALLOWEEN.

541
00:27:49,537 --> 00:27:51,452
EVERYONE GATHERS

542
00:27:51,495 --> 00:27:54,629
AND THEY GO TO THE CEMETERY
WHERE THEIR LOVED ONES
ARE BURIED.

543
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:56,936
IT'S ACTUALLY--
IT'S THE DAY AFTER
HALLOWEEN.

544
00:27:56,979 --> 00:27:59,242
SUZANNE...NO, THIS IS NOT
MORBID AT ALL, JOY.

545
00:28:00,156 --> 00:28:02,202
THIS IS CELEBRATORY,

546
00:28:02,245 --> 00:28:04,595
AND THERE'S SONG
AND DANCE,

547
00:28:04,639 --> 00:28:07,511
AND FOOD AND MUSIC
AND CANDLES.

548
00:28:07,555 --> 00:28:09,339
IT'S A REAL HOOT.

549
00:28:09,383 --> 00:28:11,559
THAT'S SWEET.
THANKS FOR THE TREATS.

550
00:28:11,602 --> 00:28:14,605
AND I'M HAVING
A  <i>DIA DE LOS MUERTOS</i>PARTY
AT MY PLACE TONIGHT.

551
00:28:14,649 --> 00:28:16,042
YOU'RE BOTH INVITED
TO COME.

552
00:28:16,085 --> 00:28:18,131
IT'S GOING TO BE
A VERY MELLOW VIBE.

553
00:28:18,174 --> 00:28:20,394
SOME TEQUILA AND FLAN.

554
00:28:21,874 --> 00:28:23,702
SOME OLDER SINGLE MEN.

555
00:28:23,745 --> 00:28:24,964
WE'LL TRY TO COME BY.

556
00:28:31,797 --> 00:28:33,973
YOU KNOW,
I WAS REMEMBERING
GEORGE TODAY,

557
00:28:34,016 --> 00:28:35,104
IN HER LITTLE
GHOST COSTUME.

558
00:28:36,802 --> 00:28:38,107
I MISS SEEING HER.

559
00:28:40,457 --> 00:28:42,329
WELL, <i>
FELIZ DIA DE LOS MUERTOS,
HONEY.</i>

560
00:28:44,810 --> 00:28:45,941
PLEASE COME.

561
00:28:53,819 --> 00:28:55,864
TWO BY TWO, KIDS.

562
00:28:55,908 --> 00:28:59,172
DO YOU SEE
HOW ANTONIO'S HOLDING
THE LION'S HAND?

563
00:28:59,215 --> 00:29:00,956
THAT'S
THE HALLOWEEN SPIRIT.

564
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:04,307
CHARLIE, IF YOU CAN'T
KEEP YOUR HANDS OFF
THAT DINOSAUR'S TAIL,

565
00:29:04,351 --> 00:29:06,092
YOU'RE GOING BACK
TO THE SHELTER EARLY.

566
00:29:09,878 --> 00:29:12,185
HEY, MAN, YOU WANT
TO GET SOME CANDY?

567
00:29:16,232 --> 00:29:17,886
WE CAN CATCH UP
WITH THEM LATER.

568
00:29:17,930 --> 00:29:21,237
DOES, UH, OH, DOES ANYONE
HAVE TO, UH, MAKE A WEE-WEE?

569
00:29:25,894 --> 00:29:28,549
TRICK OR TREAT?

570
00:29:28,592 --> 00:29:30,507
HEY, YOU'RE A CUTE GUY, HUH?
THERE YOU GO.

571
00:29:31,857 --> 00:29:34,729
THOSE ARE BOURBON CANDIES.

572
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:37,253
WELL, MY MOTHER
USED TO GIVE THEM TO ME
WHEN I WAS KID.

573
00:29:37,297 --> 00:29:38,298
SIR...

574
00:29:39,473 --> 00:29:42,171
IT'S ILLEGAL
TO GIVE ALCOHOL TO MINORS.

575
00:29:42,215 --> 00:29:44,173
AW, SHIT.

576
00:29:44,217 --> 00:29:47,133
I'M SORRY, I'M SORRY.
I JUST...
I'M SORRY.

577
00:29:47,176 --> 00:29:48,743
I JUST HATE HOLIDAYS,
YOU KNOW?

578
00:29:49,396 --> 00:29:51,833
SO GODDAMN LONELY...

579
00:29:51,877 --> 00:29:53,879
WOULD YOU MIND
TELLING ME YOUR NAME, SIR?

580
00:29:53,922 --> 00:29:55,141
LES...

581
00:29:56,533 --> 00:29:58,405
BLANDON.
SHOULD I GO GET
THE BATHROBE?

582
00:29:59,928 --> 00:30:02,017
THERE'LL BE NO ARREST
TONIGHT, MR. BLANDON.

583
00:30:02,975 --> 00:30:04,411
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

584
00:30:06,674 --> 00:30:07,806
THANK YOU.

585
00:30:09,633 --> 00:30:11,287
COME ON, PHANTOM MAN,

586
00:30:11,331 --> 00:30:12,419
LET'S HIT THE TRAILS.

587
00:30:18,773 --> 00:30:20,775
[DELORES]: THERE WE GO.
KATE, DID YOU SEE
WHICH WAY--

588
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:24,083
CHARLIE! MY GOD!

589
00:30:24,126 --> 00:30:26,520
YOU GAVE US A SCARE.

590
00:30:26,563 --> 00:30:28,652
LOSE ONE OF YOUR GROUP,
DID YOU?

591
00:30:28,696 --> 00:30:31,742
YES, AND I JUST DID
A BUDDY COUNT.[WHISTLING]

592
00:30:31,786 --> 00:30:35,355
WELL, EVERYONE'S FINE.
WHY DON'T YOU JUST MOVE ON
TO THE NEXT HOUSE, THEN?

593
00:30:35,398 --> 00:30:36,443
IS THERE
SOMETHING WRONG, OFFICER?

594
00:30:36,486 --> 00:30:38,488
IS THERE SOME CHATTER
ON THE LINE?

595
00:30:38,532 --> 00:30:41,230
NO, JUST SOME GUY
GIVING OUT BOURBON BONBONS.

596
00:30:41,274 --> 00:30:43,929
LIQUOR CHOCOLATES
WERE MY GATEWAY DRUG.

597
00:30:43,972 --> 00:30:45,756
THEY ARE NO JOKE.

598
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,019
BAG CHECK!

599
00:30:47,062 --> 00:30:48,716
LET'S SEE...

600
00:30:48,759 --> 00:30:49,673
OKAY. OKAY.

601
00:30:49,717 --> 00:30:50,979
NO JOKE.

602
00:30:51,893 --> 00:30:53,329
[WHISTLING]

603
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:58,247
OKAY...

604
00:30:58,291 --> 00:31:00,554
THANK YOU, OFFICER.

605
00:31:00,597 --> 00:31:03,557
COME ON, KIDS,
LET'S KEEP GOING.

606
00:31:04,514 --> 00:31:05,646
ANY TIME.

607
00:31:05,689 --> 00:31:08,127
THAT'S IT,
STAY CLOSE.
STAY CLOSE.

608
00:31:09,215 --> 00:31:10,433
[WHISTLING]

609
00:31:19,051 --> 00:31:20,226
THAT'S
ONE SCARY GUY.

610
00:31:20,269 --> 00:31:22,184
YEAH.

611
00:31:22,228 --> 00:31:24,491
<i>THAT'S THE THING
WITH HALLOWEEN.</i>

612
00:31:24,534 --> 00:31:27,973
<i>I WOULDN'T HAVE LOVED IT
SO MUCH IF THERE WAS NOTHING
TO BE AFRAID OF,</i>

613
00:31:28,016 --> 00:31:31,585
<i>IF SOME OF THE HOUSES
I PEERED INTO
WEREN'T HAUNTED.</i>

614
00:31:31,628 --> 00:31:33,195
YOU ALL RIGHT
THERE, CHIEF?

615
00:31:33,239 --> 00:31:34,805
YES. I AM ON A MISSION.

616
00:31:36,459 --> 00:31:37,896
OI! YOU, NO.

617
00:31:37,939 --> 00:31:40,594
THIS IS MY REAP,
AND THEREFORE,
MY DOORBELL RING.

618
00:31:41,987 --> 00:31:43,075
WELL, THEN, HAVE AT IT.

619
00:31:43,118 --> 00:31:44,293
THANK YOU.

620
00:31:44,946 --> 00:31:46,252
[RINGING]

621
00:31:47,818 --> 00:31:49,037
[SIGHS]

622
00:31:52,084 --> 00:31:53,999
THE ADDRESS AND THE TIME
ARE THE SAME.

623
00:31:54,042 --> 00:31:56,697
THAT'S KIND OF IRONIC,
ISN'T IT?

624
00:31:56,740 --> 00:31:58,742
HELLO, LITTLE MAN.
TRICK OR TREAT?

625
00:31:58,786 --> 00:32:00,005
WHAT ARE YOU?

626
00:32:00,048 --> 00:32:01,789
[COUGHING]ME? UH, WELL, UM...

627
00:32:01,832 --> 00:32:03,225
HAVE YOU EVER
HEARD OF A BRIT?

628
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:05,140
WELL, I'M A BRIT.

629
00:32:05,184 --> 00:32:07,360
SO YOU'RE A LITTLE DEVIL?

630
00:32:07,403 --> 00:32:08,883
YEAH.WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

631
00:32:09,318 --> 00:32:10,450
BOBBY.

632
00:32:10,493 --> 00:32:11,886
BOBBY, IS YOUR DAD IN?

633
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:13,279
RICHARD, OR RAYMOND, OR...

634
00:32:13,322 --> 00:32:15,542
HE WENT OUT
TO GET ME SOME
COUGH MEDICINE.

635
00:32:15,585 --> 00:32:16,760
ARE YOU SICK?

636
00:32:16,804 --> 00:32:19,198
YEAH.
NO TRICK-OR-TREATING
THIS YEAR.

637
00:32:22,766 --> 00:32:23,898
SHIT.

638
00:32:29,251 --> 00:32:32,211
NOW, YOU LITTLE DEVIL...

639
00:32:32,254 --> 00:32:36,476
I AM THINKING THAT MAYBE
YOUR PARENTS SOMETIMES
CALL YOU ROBERT,

640
00:32:38,086 --> 00:32:39,218
ROBERT PERLIS, RIGHT?

641
00:32:39,261 --> 00:32:40,393
YEAH.

642
00:32:45,789 --> 00:32:47,791
KNOW WHAT I'M GOING TO DO
FOR YOU, BOBBY?

643
00:32:47,835 --> 00:32:50,229
I AM GOING TO OPEN UP
MY BIG BAG HERE,

644
00:32:50,272 --> 00:32:52,666
AND I'M GOING TO LET YOU
PICK ANY--ANYTHING,

645
00:32:52,709 --> 00:32:54,885
ANYTHING YOU WANT,
SERIOUSLY. COME ON.

646
00:32:54,929 --> 00:32:57,018
ANYTHING.

647
00:32:57,062 --> 00:32:59,847
I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO
TAKE CANDY FROM
PEOPLE I DON'T KNOW.

648
00:32:59,890 --> 00:33:03,024
COME ON, LITTLE MAN.
YOU KNOW ME. I'M A BRIT,
I'M NOT A MONSTER, AM I?

649
00:33:03,068 --> 00:33:04,243
COME ON, CHOOSE.

650
00:33:07,463 --> 00:33:09,944
NOW, THAT IS
A BLOODY GOOD CHOICE,
BOBBY, I'M TELLING YOU.

651
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:11,902
OPEN YOUR ARMS OUT.
GO ON.

652
00:33:13,382 --> 00:33:14,514
THERE YOU GO.

653
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:21,216
THANKS.

654
00:33:22,174 --> 00:33:23,610
HEY. COME HERE.

655
00:33:26,091 --> 00:33:27,614
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.

656
00:33:28,136 --> 00:33:29,572
[COUGHING]

657
00:33:40,583 --> 00:33:41,410
HEY.

658
00:33:45,110 --> 00:33:47,025
HOW DO YOU--
HOW DO YOU THINK
HE'S GOING TO...

659
00:33:48,678 --> 00:33:49,549
HOW--

660
00:33:51,246 --> 00:33:52,465
GOD, YOU DON'T THINK
HE'S GOING TO CHOKE

661
00:33:52,508 --> 00:33:54,075
ON THAT CANDY
I GAVE HIM, DO YOU?

662
00:33:56,121 --> 00:33:57,600
[WHISTLING]

663
00:34:05,695 --> 00:34:07,349
[DOORBELL RINGING]

664
00:34:20,754 --> 00:34:22,147
[JOY]: COME ON,
GEORGE, LET'S GO.

665
00:34:26,107 --> 00:34:27,587
[WHISTLING]

666
00:34:30,155 --> 00:34:32,287
<i>THAT'S THE CONFUSING THING
ABOUT HALLOWEEN--</i>

667
00:34:34,072 --> 00:34:37,075
<i>YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO BE
A LITTLE SCARED,</i>

668
00:34:37,118 --> 00:34:40,295
<i>AND YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO OPEN YOUR DOOR
TO STRANGERS.</i>

669
00:34:40,339 --> 00:34:41,949
<i>DOES THAT MAKE ANY SENSE?</i>

670
00:34:44,169 --> 00:34:45,518
<i>WELL? DOES IT?</i>

671
00:34:48,956 --> 00:34:50,740
ALL RIGHT, LITTLE MAN,
COME WITH ME.

672
00:34:50,784 --> 00:34:51,654
YEAH.

673
00:34:54,266 --> 00:34:56,094
<i>BETTER TO BE
JUST A LITTLE SCARED.</i>

674
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:07,670
AHEM.

675
00:35:08,932 --> 00:35:10,499
HOW DO I LOOK?EMBARRASSING.

676
00:35:11,152 --> 00:35:12,675
[SIGHS]

677
00:35:12,719 --> 00:35:13,850
[SNIFFS]

678
00:35:13,894 --> 00:35:15,069
[SNIFFS AGAIN]

679
00:35:15,113 --> 00:35:16,592
WHAT IS THAT SMELL?SHIT. PUMPKIN SEEDS.

680
00:35:17,027 --> 00:35:18,203
REGGIE!

681
00:35:21,293 --> 00:35:22,772
OH! CHRIST!

682
00:35:25,210 --> 00:35:26,733
[SCREAMING]

683
00:35:36,134 --> 00:35:37,744
PUMPKIN SEEDS.

684
00:35:51,714 --> 00:35:52,802
REGGIE,
WHAT THE FUCK?

685
00:35:54,195 --> 00:35:55,675
NO NEED TO
DROP THE F-BOMB.

686
00:35:55,718 --> 00:35:57,764
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

687
00:35:57,807 --> 00:35:59,461
I FORGOT ABOUT THEM.
I'M SORRY.

688
00:35:59,505 --> 00:36:00,462
LOOK WHAT YOU DID
TO MY KITCHEN.

689
00:36:00,506 --> 00:36:02,203
I MEAN,
THIS IS A DISASTER.

690
00:36:02,812 --> 00:36:04,336
IT'S NOT.

691
00:36:04,379 --> 00:36:06,076
REGGIE, THIS IS
UNBELIEVABLE!

692
00:36:06,120 --> 00:36:07,687
WORSE THINGS
HAVE HAPPENED, MOM.

693
00:36:12,082 --> 00:36:14,824
YOU ALWAYS GO CRAZY
OVER THE STUFF
THAT DOESN'T EVEN MATTER.

694
00:36:23,746 --> 00:36:25,879
OKAY, THEN WHY DON'T YOU
PUT ON A COSTUME

695
00:36:25,922 --> 00:36:28,360
AND COME WITH ME,
OVER TO SUZANNE'S PARTY?

696
00:36:28,403 --> 00:36:29,535
I WANT TO STAY HERE.

697
00:36:29,578 --> 00:36:31,885
JUST COME WITH ME.

698
00:36:31,928 --> 00:36:33,539
I'LL STAY HERE
AND HAND OUT CANDY.

699
00:36:33,582 --> 00:36:35,410
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A VERY GOOD IDEA.

700
00:36:36,368 --> 00:36:37,804
IT'S JUST HALLOWEEN, MOM.

701
00:36:39,719 --> 00:36:40,763
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

702
00:36:42,069 --> 00:36:42,939
FINE.

703
00:36:49,598 --> 00:36:51,034
I'LL HAVE
MY PHONE WITH ME.

704
00:36:51,078 --> 00:36:53,080
[BEEP]IT'S ON, OKAY?

705
00:36:53,123 --> 00:36:55,038
OKAY.

706
00:36:55,082 --> 00:36:58,041
I'LL COME BACK SOON,
AND THEN WE CAN...

707
00:36:59,826 --> 00:37:02,307
WE CAN ANSWER THE DOOR
TOGETHER, OKAY?

708
00:37:02,916 --> 00:37:04,047
SURE.

709
00:37:06,746 --> 00:37:08,443
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

710
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:10,228
IT'LL BE A HOOT.

711
00:37:19,933 --> 00:37:23,284
<i>I DON'T REMEMBER
EVERY SINGLE MOMENT
ABOUT BEING A KID...</i>

712
00:37:23,328 --> 00:37:25,330
<i>BUT I SURE
REMEMBER HALLOWEEN.</i>

713
00:37:26,940 --> 00:37:28,942
<i>THE STUFF
THAT SENT MY HEART RACING</i>

714
00:37:28,985 --> 00:37:32,119
<i>HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH
GHOULS OR GOBLINS
OR WITCHES</i>

715
00:37:32,162 --> 00:37:34,600
<i>OR EVEN GHOSTS.</i>

716
00:37:34,643 --> 00:37:38,778
<i>THE STUFF THAT SCARED ME
WAS WHAT WAS LURKING BEHIND
ALL THOSE CLOSED DOORS,</i>

717
00:37:38,821 --> 00:37:41,084
<i>ALL THOSE SECRETS
HIDING IN THE DARK...</i>

718
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:49,615
[♪♪]

719
00:37:55,534 --> 00:37:58,450
<i>YOU REALLY WANT TO KNOW
HOW TO SCARE THE CRAP
OUT OF YOURSELF?</i>

720
00:37:58,493 --> 00:38:00,669
<i>SOME HALLOWEEN NIGHT,
GO RING THE WRONG DOORBELL.</i>

721
00:38:02,802 --> 00:38:04,369
[DOORBELL RINGING]

722
00:38:06,980 --> 00:38:08,373
YES?

723
00:38:08,416 --> 00:38:11,680
WHY DON'T YOU GIVE OUT CANDY
LIKE A NORMAL PERSON?

724
00:38:11,724 --> 00:38:16,642
WELL, YOUNG LADY,
I LEFT A BOWL,
AND YOU KICKED IT OVER.

725
00:38:16,685 --> 00:38:18,252
[JOY]: COME ON,
GEORGE, LET'S GO!

726
00:38:19,645 --> 00:38:21,429
GEORGIA, COME ON!

727
00:38:22,169 --> 00:38:23,649
I HAVE TO GO.

728
00:38:23,692 --> 00:38:25,433
ALL RIGHT.

729
00:38:25,477 --> 00:38:27,087
BUT COME BACK
NEXT YEAR.

730
00:38:29,394 --> 00:38:33,180
<i>IF MOST PEOPLE KNEW
HOW MANY TIMES
THEY BRUSHED BY DEATH,</i>

731
00:38:33,223 --> 00:38:36,662
<i>THEY'D PROBABLY STAY INSIDE
FOR THE REST OF THEIR LIVES.</i>

732
00:38:40,013 --> 00:38:42,885
<i>OR AT LEAST THEY WOULDN'T
KNOCK ON THIS DARK DOOR.</i>

733
00:38:52,547 --> 00:38:53,983
TRICK OR TREAT.

734
00:38:54,984 --> 00:38:56,508
I DON'T HAVE ANY CANDY.

735
00:38:57,726 --> 00:38:59,075
I SEE YOUR CANDY
RIGHT THERE.

736
00:39:06,213 --> 00:39:07,388
I KNOW YOU.

737
00:39:13,699 --> 00:39:14,874
IT'S DONE.

738
00:39:16,441 --> 00:39:17,833
IT'S ALL OVER.

739
00:39:23,361 --> 00:39:24,840
WHO ARE YOU?

740
00:39:26,407 --> 00:39:27,887
NOBODY
YOU WANT TO KNOW.

741
00:39:35,938 --> 00:39:38,463
<i>I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW HE WAS GOING TO DIE.</i>

742
00:39:38,506 --> 00:39:42,467
<i>AND TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
I REALLY DIDN'T GIVE A SHIT.</i>

743
00:39:42,510 --> 00:39:44,382
<i>SOME OF THE DEAD
ARE JUST BETTER LEFT
FORGOTTEN.</i>

744
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:54,740
REGGIE, WE CAN GO
BACK TO THE PARTY,

745
00:39:56,263 --> 00:39:57,395
WE CAN GO HOME...

746
00:40:00,310 --> 00:40:01,790
I'LL DO
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

747
00:40:01,834 --> 00:40:04,445
I AM JUST
NOT COMFORTABLE...

748
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:07,274
HERE.

749
00:40:09,276 --> 00:40:10,408
IT'S TOO DISTURBING.

750
00:40:13,715 --> 00:40:15,978
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE
DISTURBING.

751
00:40:16,022 --> 00:40:18,720
IT'S HALLOWEEN
IN A GRAVEYARD.

752
00:40:18,764 --> 00:40:20,026
IT'S THE DAY
OF THE DEAD.

753
00:40:21,941 --> 00:40:23,508
YOU KNOW, REGGIE,
ACTUALLY,

754
00:40:23,551 --> 00:40:26,293
<i>DIA DE LOS MUERTOS
IS TOMORROW.</i>

755
00:40:27,816 --> 00:40:29,992
SUZANNE SAID
IT'S THE ONE DAY

756
00:40:30,036 --> 00:40:31,559
WHEN SPIRITS
VISIT THE EARTH.

757
00:40:31,603 --> 00:40:33,779
YEAH, AND THAT ONE DAY
IS ACTUALLY TOMORROW,

758
00:40:33,822 --> 00:40:35,694
AS IN THE DAYTIME, HMM?

759
00:40:36,782 --> 00:40:39,045
AND SUZANNE
SMOKES A LOT OF POT.

760
00:40:39,915 --> 00:40:40,873
LET'S GO HOME.

761
00:40:48,707 --> 00:40:50,883
YOU DIDN'T EVEN
GO TRICK-OR-TREATING
THIS YEAR.

762
00:40:53,538 --> 00:40:54,452
THAT MAKES ME SAD.

763
00:40:55,931 --> 00:40:58,456
I'M DONE WITH IT.

764
00:40:58,499 --> 00:41:00,806
IS IT BECAUSE GEORGE
ALWAYS USED TO TAKE YOU
TRICK-OR-TREATING?

765
00:41:04,853 --> 00:41:06,115
AND IGNORED ME.

766
00:41:15,298 --> 00:41:16,474
COME HERE.

767
00:41:18,911 --> 00:41:20,608
COME KEEP
YOUR MOTHER WARM.

768
00:41:37,756 --> 00:41:40,323
FUCKING BULLSHIT.
I DON'T LIKE
ALMONDS AND COCONUT

769
00:41:40,367 --> 00:41:41,150
IN MY CHOCOLATE.

770
00:41:41,194 --> 00:41:42,587
I DO.

771
00:41:42,630 --> 00:41:44,066
MAKE ME AN OFFER.

772
00:41:44,110 --> 00:41:47,243
UH, MILK DUDS
AND A CANDY BAR
TO BE NAMED LATER?

773
00:41:47,287 --> 00:41:49,245
OKAY.

774
00:41:49,289 --> 00:41:51,204
BLACK LICORICE--
TOTALLY GROSS.
WHO WANTS TO TRADE?

775
00:41:57,123 --> 00:41:58,951
FINE.
BE THAT WAY.

776
00:42:00,648 --> 00:42:01,954
[GROWLS]

777
00:42:04,130 --> 00:42:07,699
HEY, RUBE, SURE
YOU DON'T WANT ANYTHING?

778
00:42:08,656 --> 00:42:10,092
HALLOWEEN'S FOR KIDS.

779
00:42:10,136 --> 00:42:11,529
YOU GUYS HAVE IT.

780
00:42:11,572 --> 00:42:13,879
I HAVE TO ADMIT, MASON,
THIS IS
AN IMPRESSIVE HAUL.

781
00:42:13,922 --> 00:42:15,837
THANK YOU VERY MUCH, DAISY.

782
00:42:15,881 --> 00:42:18,361
YOU MUST'VE
REALLY WORKED HARD.

783
00:42:18,405 --> 00:42:19,319
YOU DON'T KNOW.

784
00:42:19,972 --> 00:42:21,539
ANYWAY, THANKS.

785
00:42:21,582 --> 00:42:22,801
YOU'RE WELCOME.

786
00:42:26,456 --> 00:42:27,849
COME ON, RUBE.

787
00:42:27,893 --> 00:42:29,590
I KNOW
YOU LOVE SWEETS.
HAVE SOMETHING.

788
00:42:31,418 --> 00:42:33,115
I WOULDN'T MIND
A LITTLE PEANUT
BRITTLE, PEANUT.

789
00:42:36,162 --> 00:42:39,426
THAT'S NOT WHO I AM ANYMORE,
I'M NOT THAT GIRL.

790
00:42:40,645 --> 00:42:42,603
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

791
00:42:42,647 --> 00:42:44,344
WELL, HAPPY HALLOWEEN
ANYWAY...

792
00:42:45,606 --> 00:42:46,825
PEANUT.

793
00:42:49,479 --> 00:42:51,612
WELL, IT'S NOT
HALLOWEEN ANYMORE.
IT'S TOMORROW.

794
00:42:51,656 --> 00:42:52,831
ALL SAINTS' DAY.

795
00:42:52,874 --> 00:42:54,920
IS THAT
A SPECIAL ONE, TOO?

796
00:42:54,963 --> 00:42:56,791
DO I HAVE TO WEAR A MASK?

797
00:42:56,835 --> 00:43:01,883
LEGEND HAS IT THAT SPIRITS
GATHER IN GRAVEYARDS
ON ALL SAINTS' DAY.

798
00:43:01,927 --> 00:43:03,015
THAT'S WHERE
THEY HONOR THE DEAD.

799
00:43:03,058 --> 00:43:04,625
HOW WILL YOU
BE SPENDING IT?

800
00:43:06,235 --> 00:43:07,628
IN A GRAVEYARD.

801
00:43:08,760 --> 00:43:10,413
GOOD NIGHT, GUYS.

802
00:43:10,457 --> 00:43:11,284
BYE.

803
00:43:11,763 --> 00:43:13,199
[SNARLING]

804
00:43:16,419 --> 00:43:17,812
[GROWLING]

805
00:43:19,248 --> 00:43:21,468
<i>I ALWAYS THOUGHT
I LOVED HALLOWEEN</i>

806
00:43:21,511 --> 00:43:25,428
<i>BECAUSE I GOT TO LOOK BEHIND
ALL THOSE CLOSED DOORS,</i>

807
00:43:25,472 --> 00:43:30,651
<i>BUT NOW I SEE THAT IT'S
BECAUSE I WAS PAINTED
WITH SOMETHING DARKER...</i>

808
00:43:30,695 --> 00:43:34,786
<i>THAT I WAS MEANT
TO SEE THE DARK,
AND THROUGH THE DARK...</i>

809
00:44:07,732 --> 00:44:09,777
<i>I'M NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE...</i>

810
00:44:10,691 --> 00:44:12,737
<i>BUT I AM.</i>

811
00:44:12,780 --> 00:44:15,043
<i>I DON'T KNOW
IF I'M SUPPOSED TO
WATCH OVER THEM,</i>

812
00:44:16,001 --> 00:44:18,264
<i>OR JUST HAUNT THEM.</i>

813
00:44:42,723 --> 00:44:45,987
<i>EITHER WAY, I'D BE LYING
IF I SAID I WASN'T
HAVING FUN.</i>

814
00:44:47,510 --> 00:44:50,383
<i>I'D BE LYING IF I SAID
I DIDN'T WANT TO BE HERE...</i>

815
00:44:53,125 --> 00:44:56,781
<i>WALKING THROUGH A GRAVEYARD
THE DAY AFTER HALLOWEEN,</i>

816
00:44:56,824 --> 00:44:59,784
<i>ON A QUIET AND BEAUTIFUL
NOVEMBER MORNING...</i>

817
00:45:00,741 --> 00:45:02,700
<i>IT'S NOT SO BAD...</i>

818
00:45:02,743 --> 00:45:04,310
<i>BEING DEAD LIKE ME.</i>

